\h #dPOSSESS \d

\uUSAGE\n
#dpossess ID

\uDESCRIPTION\n
Temporarily take control of an NPC.

Note the following:
* You will continue to see text sent to your admin PC as usual.2`
* Text generated by the actions of a third party and sent to the NPC you possess is prefixed with \t \d. (The intent is to make this text easily distinguishable from text sent to your admin PC.)2`
* The NPC's prompt is likewise prefixed with \t \d.2`

Once you have begun possessing an NPC, type \q?\d to see what commands are available to you, and \qexorcise\d to stop possessing.

\uEXAMPLES\n
\q#dpossess 100\d to possess ID 100.4`

\uSEE ALSO\n
